{"id":"1303.2851","submitter":"Hugo Touchette","authors":"Giacomo Gradenigo, Alessandro Sarracino, Andrea Puglisi, Hugo\n  Touchette","title":"Fluctuation relations without uniform large deviations","comments":"12 pages, 1 figure; v2: published version","journal-ref":"J. Phys. A: Math. Theor. 46, 335002, 2013","doi":"10.1088/1751-8113/46/33/335002","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.stat-mech","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We study the fluctuations of a stochastic Maxwell-Lorentz particle model\ndriven by an external field to determine the extent to which fluctuation\nrelations are related to large deviations. Focusing on the total entropy\nproduction of this model in its steady state, we show that, although the\nprobability density of this quantity globally satisfies (by definition) a\nfluctuation relation, its negative tail decays exponentially with time, whereas\nits positive tail decays slower than exponentially with time because of long\ncollision-free trajectories. This provides an example of physical system for\nwhich the fluctuation relation does not derive, as commonly thought, from a\nprobability density decaying everywhere exponentially with time or, in other\nwords, from a probability density having a uniform large deviation form.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Mar 2013 11:42:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Aug 2013 14:50:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-08-02"}
